HOW TO USE
- create a copy of build.properties.template named build.properties  
- edit build.properties
- use ant to compile and run the project either from the console or with your ide
- to specify the class to run you can change the 
  
  siris.propfile.classname 

  property in the build.properties file or add an additional argument to ant in the console 
  (run ant without a target to see the usage info)

HINT
- intellij supports external ant files and can pass properties from within the ide 
  pass a property 

  siris.ide.classname

  via intellij to specify which what to run when invoking a "run" target
